{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/posts/theres-nothing-quite-like-anime-1825312911/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Reikaze Rambles","siteUrl":"https://reikazerambles.com","disqusShortname":"reikazerambles","repoPath":"Reikaze/Reikaze.github.io","relativeToPosts":"/content/blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"186f611a-b484-5985-b776-9b16bc53d624","excerpt":"There’s nothing quite like the feeling of binging a show you adore, or watching\n  all the new releases. It makes youe excited to tell the next person about this…","html":"<div><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf\" title=\"ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf\" src=\"/static/4ffa34bd5d0b540f17cf799852e0429f/1c72d/ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/4ffa34bd5d0b540f17cf799852e0429f/a80bd/ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf.jpg 148w,\n/static/4ffa34bd5d0b540f17cf799852e0429f/1c91a/ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf.jpg 295w,\n/static/4ffa34bd5d0b540f17cf799852e0429f/1c72d/ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf.jpg 590w,\n/static/4ffa34bd5d0b540f17cf799852e0429f/a8a14/ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf.jpg 885w,\n/static/4ffa34bd5d0b540f17cf799852e0429f/fbd2c/ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf.jpg 1180w,\n/static/4ffa34bd5d0b540f17cf799852e0429f/eea4a/ghnrpbty6ihbmzrjgfsf.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span><p class=\"sc-77igqf-0 bOfvBY\">There&#x2019;s nothing quite like watching Anime. <br></p><p class=\"sc-77igqf-0 bOfvBY\">\n<br>A few years ago, I used to watch at least a dozen anime a season, and I kept up with all of them. But, as I&#x2019;ve\n  gone through the trying times of college, I&#x2019;ve found that I&#x2019;ve had less and less time: With the constant bombarding of\n  work, school, and other related life related tasks, priorities have been shifted, and anime has been shafted. From\n  Dozens a week, to a handful. From some a week, to one a week. From once a week, to maybe once a month. While this\n  might not seem like anything special, as everyone has cycles in their hobbies, this lapse in anime has made me think\n  about my relationship to this hobby we all share, and honestly, all I can say is that... Anime, how I long for thee.\n</p>\n<div class=\"bxm4mm-2 hKBnez js_video-sticky__top-limit\"></div>\n<div class=\"bxm4mm-4 fQqUFt\"></div></div>\n<div class=\"bxm4mm-1 gKeXmA js_video-sticky-trigger\"></div>\n<div class=\"bxm4mm-0 jRTmst instream-native-video instream-permalink js_video-sticky-target instream-native-video--mobile\"></div>\n\n<div class=\"bxm4mm-3 eCMXYG js_video-sticky__bottom-limit\"></div>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg\" title=\"twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg\" src=\"/static/531bed790efa436602aded569e21091b/fcda8/twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg.png\" srcset=\"/static/531bed790efa436602aded569e21091b/12f09/twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg.png 148w,\n/static/531bed790efa436602aded569e21091b/e4a3f/twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg.png 295w,\n/static/531bed790efa436602aded569e21091b/fcda8/twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg.png 590w,\n/static/531bed790efa436602aded569e21091b/efc66/twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg.png 885w,\n/static/531bed790efa436602aded569e21091b/c83ae/twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg.png 1180w,\n/static/531bed790efa436602aded569e21091b/21b4d/twdnbxlm0vjazb8sgpxg.png 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span><p class=\"sc-77igqf-0 bOfvBY\">I&#x2019;ve always heard of people describe anime as a form of escapism, but I&#x2019;ve never\n  really thought of it as that for me personally. Sure, with all the isekai and fantastic worlds, anime can easily be\n  that way, but that was never the point of anime for me: Anime wasn&#x2019;t to avoid issues of reality, so much as it was for\n  the the feeling of engagement. This medium has lead to some of the most memorable experiences in my life and has lead\n  to levels of engagement I&#x2019;ve never really felt otherwise. Anime, even when you aren&#x2019;t looking to drown reality with,\n  can feel more real than real life, and that&#x2019;s a truly amazing thing. <br> <br>My time away from anime has taught me\n  about the nature of introversion - I&#x2019;ve always thought of myself is an introvert but being away from anime has\n  reaffirmed that for me. Introversion and extroversion is about one&#x2019;s natural state and being away from anime has\n  reminded me of how much I enjoy the hobby, how it&#x2019;s been embedded in the way I live my life. These hobbies are more\n  than just hobbies, they are my ideal natural state and I&#x2019;m sure that&#x2019;s the same for many other people here.<br></p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"hqp0hy4ncpvae48rg5ot\" title=\"hqp0hy4ncpvae48rg5ot\" src=\"/static/cede0c7fd6a1214a9283f82073a8a2ce/1c72d/hqp0hy4ncpvae48rg5ot.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/cede0c7fd6a1214a9283f82073a8a2ce/a80bd/hqp0hy4ncpvae48rg5ot.jpg 148w,\n/static/cede0c7fd6a1214a9283f82073a8a2ce/1c91a/hqp0hy4ncpvae48rg5ot.jpg 295w,\n/static/cede0c7fd6a1214a9283f82073a8a2ce/1c72d/hqp0hy4ncpvae48rg5ot.jpg 590w,\n/static/cede0c7fd6a1214a9283f82073a8a2ce/4b190/hqp0hy4ncpvae48rg5ot.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span><p class=\"sc-77igqf-0 bOfvBY\">There’s nothing quite like the feeling of binging a show you adore, or watching\nall the new releases. It makes youe excited to tell the next person about this wonderful thing you’ve just saw.... and\nwatching some of these fantastic shows in this season has reminded me of that. So, I have to say to you, If you love\nanime, don’t forget about it! Sit back and relax with some <em>Yuru Camp, </em>have your heart ripped out by PTSD in\n<em>Steins;Gate 0</em> or get hyped with <em>My Hero Academia</em>. It’s a wonderful hobby, and I’m glad I can share\nit with all of you. I thank everyone who reads this for being an awesome aspect of the anime community, and once I get\nsome more time to engage myself with anime and everything that surrounds it, I hope I can write some more about these\nthings we love so dearly. Sorry for being gone for so long, thank you very much for being awsome!</p></p>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"There's Nothing Quite Like Watching Anime","published":"April 17, 2018","tags":["AniTay","Anime"],"description":null,"oldArticle":true,"authors":[{"name":"Kevin Mai","id":"reikaze","description":"Hello! I'm Kevin Phong Mai, aka Reikaze or RockmanDash12, a Computer Engineering Student and Freelance Writer passionate about Tech, Anime, Visual Novels and much more. I'm the Owner of RockmanDash Reviews Blog, and I write for the AniTAY & FuwaNovel blogs.","color":"#ba68c8","socials":{"twitter":"Reikaze0"},"profileImg":{"childImageSharp":{"smallPic":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":60,"height":60,"src":"/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/c28c8/kevin.jpg","srcSet":"/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/c28c8/kevin.jpg 1x,\n/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/8bc16/kevin.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/b2712/kevin.jpg 2x"},"mediumPic":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":85,"height":85,"src":"/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/97a9c/kevin.jpg","srcSet":"/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/97a9c/kevin.jpg 1x,\n/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/6d25d/kevin.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/b119b/kevin.jpg 2x"},"bigPic":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":300,"height":300,"src":"/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/88b18/kevin.jpg","srcSet":"/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/88b18/kevin.jpg 1x,\n/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/86c85/kevin.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/46fb546e9b0c6240a8385f7cac6794a2/c3638/kevin.jpg 2x"}}}}]},"fields":{"slug":"/theres-nothing-quite-like-anime-1825312911/"},"wordCount":{"words":165}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/theres-nothing-quite-like-anime-1825312911/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/rockmandashs-top-anime-of-2017-1822289215/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"RockmanDash's Top Anime of 2017","oldArticle":true,"authors":[{"id":"reikaze"}]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/a-call-for-transparency-and-the-issue-with-steams-eroge-1826128670/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"A Call for Transparency and the Issue with Steam's Eroge(?) Purge","oldArticle":true,"authors":[{"id":"reikaze"}]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["151170173"]}